## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="3f532-102">Puede obtener información de identificación de un motor de reconocimiento inicializado con <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RecognizerInfo%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> para un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> objeto o <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.RecognizerInfo%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> para un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> objeto.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3f532-102">You can obtain identifying information for an initialized recognition engine using <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.RecognizerInfo%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> for a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> object or <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.RecognizerInfo%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> for a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> object.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="3f532-103">Devuelve la información de las instancias de <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizerInfo> obtenida una <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> viene determinada por la configuración de la **propiedades de voz** miembro de la **Panel de Control**.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3f532-103">The information returned in instances of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizerInfo> obtained from a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> is determined by the settings in the **Speech Properties** member of the **Control Panel**.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="3f532-104">Puede usar instancias de <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizerInfo> para construir una configuración específica de <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> utilizando el <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.%23ctor%28System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizerInfo%29> constructor.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3f532-104">You can use instances of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizerInfo> to construct a specific configuration of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> using the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.%23ctor%28System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizerInfo%29> constructor.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="3f532-105">El método estático <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.InstalledRecognizers%2A> devuelve una lista de todos los disponibles <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> configuraciones como <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizerInfo> instancias.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3f532-105">The static method <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.InstalledRecognizers%2A> returns a list of all available <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> configurations as <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizerInfo> instances.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="3f532-106">El siguiente ejemplo valida un determinado <xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo> y cadena de identificador en función de los permitidos <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> configuraciones, expresadas como una lista de <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizerInfo> objetos.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3f532-106">The following example validates a given <xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo> and identifier string against the permitted <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> configurations, expressed as a list of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizerInfo> objects.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="3f532-107">Si el <xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo> y cadena de identificador son válidos, el ejemplo crea una nueva instancia de <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> utilizando el <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizerInfo> instancia como un argumento.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3f532-107">If the <xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo> and identifier string are valid, the example creates a new instance of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> using the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizerInfo> instance as an argument.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
  
private SpeechRecognitionEngine SelectRecognizer(CultureInfo requiredCulture, string requiredId)   
{  
  // Select based on a specific recognizer configuration  
  SpeechRecognitionEngine speechRecognitionEngine=null;  
  foreach (RecognizerInfo config in SpeechRecognitionEngine.InstalledRecognizers())   
  {  
    if (config.Culture.Equals(requiredCulture) && config.Id== requiredId)   
    {  
      speechRecognitionEngine = new SpeechRecognitionEngine(config);  
      break;  
    }  
  }  
  return speechRecognitionEngine;  
}  
```

  
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="3f532-110">El ejemplo siguiente implementa un clic de botón que muestra toda la información en un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizerInfo> objeto en un <xref:System.Windows.Forms.MessageBox>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3f532-110">The example below implements a button click which displays all the information in a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizerInfo> object in a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.MessageBox>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="3f532-111">Los pares clave-valor incluidos en el <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IDictionary%602> instancia devuelta por <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizerInfo.AdditionalInfo%2A> se concatenan en una tabla de texto.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3f532-111">The key/value pairs contained in the <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IDictionary%602> instance returned by <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizerInfo.AdditionalInfo%2A> are concatenated into a text table.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
private void recognizerInfoButton_Click(object sender, EventArgs e)   
{  
  RecognizerInfo info = _recognizer.RecognizerInfo;  
  string AudioFormats = "";  
  foreach (SpeechAudioFormatInfo fmt in info.SupportedAudioFormats)   
  {  
    AudioFormats += String.Format("       {0}\n", fmt.EncodingFormat.ToString());  
  }  
  string AdditionalInfo = "";  
  foreach (string key in info.AdditionalInfo.Keys)   
  {  
    AdditionalInfo += String.Format("      {0}: {1}\n", key, info.AdditionalInfo[key]);  
  }  
  MessageBox.Show(String.Format(  
                     "Name:                 {0 } \n" +  
                     "Description:          {1} \n" +  
                     "SupportedAudioFormats:\n" +  
                     " {2} " +  
                     "Culture:              {3} \n" +  
                     "AdditionalInfo:       \n" +  
                     " {4}\n",  
                     info.Name.ToString(),  
                     info.Description.ToString(),  
                     AudioFormats,  
                     info.Culture.ToString(),  
                     AdditionalInfo));  
}  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="3f532-114">Un <xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo> objeto puede incluir el nombre de la referencia cultural, el idioma asociado, el país o región, el calendario usado y cómo dar formato a fechas y ordenar cadenas.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3f532-114">A <xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo> object can include the name of the culture, the associated language, the country/region, the calendar used, and how to format dates and sort strings.</span></span>  
  
   
  
